@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "Shareware"
@prev "Requirements"

@{fg shine}Usage@{fg text}

I  think there's no need for many words.  Usage is very simple.  Each of the
program gadgets correspondent to one of MultiCX tooltypes.  See @{"MultiCX" link "Thanks" 0} docs
for further informations.

Supports version of MultiCX upto 2.79.

MUI_MCX_Prefs  tries  to open MultiCX's .info file to get the tooltypes.  If
it can't get access then TEST gadget is disabled and some default values are
set.   Now  actual  settings  can  be saved to any .info file.  When running
MultiCX  while  MUI_MCX_Prefs is running all settings will be overwritten by
the values from MultiCX tooltypes.

All  gadgets  are mouse or keyboard controlled.  You can also use TAB key to
jump  from  one gadget to the next.  To change page use CRSR UP or CRSR down
keys or use mouse.

SAVE   - save the settings to  MultiCX or any .info file when MultiCX is not 
         running.

TEST   - save the actual settings to MultiCX. Old tooltypes will be restored
         when  leaving  by  CANCEL  gadget  or  window close gadget. Unknown 
         tooltypes will we restored as well.

QUIT   - Finish Program. (Restore old  tooltypes if you used TEST before.)


You can use tooltype MULTICXPATH=<path> for path to find MultiCX. Use same 
as argument when running from CLI.  Otherwise  MultiCX  can't  be launched 
from  program. If  the path  contains some spaces  You have to put it into 
brackets '"'!

You  can use tooltype  LANGUAGE=<language>  to overwrite the settings from 
Your preferences. Use same as argument when running from CLI. If the catalog
can't be loaded the buildin (english) texts will be used instead.
@endnode

